programme.desc: Christina has been experiencing paranormal activity ever since her father and step-mother were murdered near Columbus, OH last year. PRS and psychic/medium?Chip Coffey delve into a open murder case and wind up exposing a family divide.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Dark Practice
programme.desc: Brenda is terrified by a dark hooded figure spotted in her West Virginia home. The same entity allegedly tormented her late husband. PRS and Psychic/Medium Michelle Belanger help Brenda before she slips into the same abyss as her late husband.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Southern Discomfort At Sweetwater Mansion
programme.desc: PRS heads to the Deep South to investigate a haunted Antebellum Mansion in disrepair. The caretaker and volunteers at the property have many a tale to tell of paranormal activity.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Sickness
programme.desc: Something is making Lisa and her family sick. Is it natural or paranormal? Ryan and the team uncover the tragic history surrounding Lisa's home--with shocking connections to respiratory illness.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Haunted Ranch
programme.desc: PRS saddles up to a remote ranch in Hunt, Texas where black shadows are being spotted and animals harmed. What's more, a mysterious crop circle has formed on the property and the horses refuse to cross it.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Who Is the Lurking Man?
programme.desc: PRS travels to Newcastle, CA to investigate a house with paranormal forces so strong, the family has cleared out. Ryan believes the Native American land may hold the key to the mystery and leads the team in a fight to reclaim a scared family's house.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Invitation to Evil
programme.desc: Paula and her husband Mike are under siege by a purported shadow demon in their North Carolina home. Paula has witnessed a toddler bed levitating and heard deep growls. Michelle, Ryan and the team uncover the shocking truth behind the haunting.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Haunted Piano
programme.desc: Ryan and the PRS team are called in when unlucky antique collectors unwittingly bring a paranormally-infested piano into their home. The team attempts to dismantle and destroy the offending instrument.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Plas Mawr, Conwy, North Wales
programme.desc: The team visits a barren Elizabethan townhouse occupied by the spirits of its 16th-century inhabitants. Did a woman tragically die here? Is a disgraced doctor still trapped in a bricked-up chimney?

programme.title: Most Haunted: Margam Castle, Port Talbot, South Wales
programme.desc: Yvette and the team visit the imposing Margam Castle. Are the bumps and bangs they hear the ghosts of playful Victorian children and a malevolent gamekeeper who was murdered within these grounds?
programme.sub-title: Margam Castle, Port Talbot, South Wales

programme.title: Most Haunted: Ancient High House, Stafford
programme.desc: The team investigates ghostly sightings at England's largest surviving Tudor townhouse. It may have been inhabited for 400 years, but who is responsible for the apparitions plaguing visitors today?

programme.title: Most Haunted: Royal Exchange Theatre, Manchester
programme.desc: Battered by WWII and IRA bomb blasts, the Royal Exchange has risen from the ashes to show real signs of paranormal activity. Remnants of its former guise as a trading center draw the team there.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Preston Manor, Brighton
programme.desc: Behind Preston Manor's austere appearance lies the murder of a nun several centuries ago, and one of Britain's oldest hauntings. The "Most Haunted" team investigates.

programme.title: Most Haunted: North East Aircraft Museum, Sunderland
programme.desc: World War battles have left an indelible mark on this former airfield. As the crew enter the museum, they encounter the ghosts of two military figures: one a hero, the other a traitor.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Taunton Castle
programme.desc: The malicious energies of the "Hanging Judge" still resonate throughout Taunton Castle. A modern mystery also awaits the team, which leads to a night full of panic and intense poltergeist activity.

programme.title: Most Haunted: East Riddlesden Hall, Keighley, West Yorkshire
programme.desc: Little is known of East Riddlesden Hall's claims of paranormal activity. However, worrying events cause the team to fear the worst as darkness descends over this isolated and eerie home.
programme.sub-title: East Riddlesden Hall, Keighley, West Yorkshire

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: It's a Dog's Life
programme.desc: Mark believes that God has turned Jonathan into a dog. Meanwhile, he must contend with a runaway kid and the kid's scatterbrained mother.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Merry Christmas from Grandpa
programme.desc: On Christmas Eve, Jonathan shows three men what will happen in the future if the Earth continues to be ravaged by pollution. One of the men is an energy official another is a farmer and the third one is the President.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Pilot - Part 1
programme.desc: In the series opener, we meet Jonathan Smith, a probationary angel who has been sent to help people on Earth. He befriends residents at a retirement home. The administrator at the home has a brother named Mark who is suspicious of Jonathan.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Pilot - Part 2
programme.desc: Jonathan helps the residents of Havencrest, when they learn that the retirement home is going to be sold. Jonathan must reveal his real identity to Mark in order to complete the assignment.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: To Touch The Moon
programme.desc: Jonathan helps a terminally ill boy and his mother. Meanwhile, Mark deals with a thief abandoned by his folks.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Return of the Masked Rider
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark help aging movie heroes to stand up to a street gang known as Satan's Helpers. They persuade a young boxer not to throw a big fight when the gang tries to bully him.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Song of the Wild West
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark assist a young country singer who is hoping to follow in her mother's footsteps. Next, they help a widow mourning her late husband.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Bernie Sharp
programme.desc: Presenter and stylist Nicky Hambleton-Jones uses every trick in the book to make someone look dramatically younger. What will it take to transform the bedraggled and drawn features of prison officer Bernie Sharp?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Sharon Evans
programme.desc: 45 year old Welsh farmer Sharon Evans has so many animals to tend to that she's stopped looking after herself. Nicky Hambleton-Jones calls in the full cavalry on this one. Standby for one of the most breathtaking transformations of the series.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Oh, To Be a Kid Again!
programme.desc: Katrina dropped out of school and became a needed parent to her younger siblings. Her looks went south and her social life became non-existent, so Katrina turned to food for comfort. Time to make Katrina look 10 Years Younger!
programme.sub-title: Oh, To Be a Kid Again!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Turning That Frown Upside Down
programme.desc: Angela's made such a habit of hiding her discolored teeth that she's developed a permanent frown. She's pursuing a career as a comedienne, but it's hard for her to laugh about the state of her looks. She feels like the clock is ticking.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: From Stache to Flash
programme.desc: Jerry, a caring husband, father of three, and new grandfather, has been hiding his teeth behind a moustache for years! With his style stuck in the 70's, it's our goal to help Jerry flash forward as we try to make Jerry look 10 Years Younger!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Carole Ward
programme.desc: Nicky Hambleton-Jones and the team come to the rescue of 47-year-old Carole Ward who feels very unglamorous.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: From Scrubs to Stilettos
programme.desc: Lisa works double shifts as a nurse and is also a single mom to a teenage son. After burning the candle at both ends for so long, it is finally showing up in her appearance. Our team is going to give this busy career mom some serious pampering.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Breaking Ground On A New Look
programme.desc: Dane's been working in the sun without coverage since he was 14 years old, and hasn't been to the dentist in 13 years. He's a derm and dental bad boy who needs to be scared straight, not only for himself, but for his daughters and fianc as well.
programme.sub-title: Breaking Ground On A New Look

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Starting Over
programme.desc: Elyse is a recently divorced mother of two, trying to start her new life. She has found it difficult to stay in shape, and feels stress, UV rays and time have caught up with her. Now ready to re-enter the dating game, our coaches help get her into shape.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Runaway Ready
programme.desc: Joslyn modeled in college, and was a woman who always took care of the way she looked. After becoming a mother, the years of neglect have caught up to her. Will our experts be able to make Joslyn runway ready?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: No Time For Dad
programme.desc: David is a fire captain at work and has a wife and seven kids at home. His responsibilities have taken their toll, and he feels like an old man of the firehouse. Can David's look go from lukewarm to smoldering?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Janice Holmes
programme.desc: Wife and mother, Janice Holmes,42, was used to living it large. Then she lost more than three stone in weight, and stubbed out her forty-a-day fag habit, to become a picture of health.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Kim Edgecombe
programme.desc: Fiona McDonald and the "10 Years" team of experts gear up for their toughest challenge yet! Kim Edgecombe is living proof that smoking really does cause premature aging. Kim needs help, but are the team too late?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Heather Williams Re-Visit
programme.desc: Nicky Hambleton-Jones revisits 42-year-old Heather Williams from Essex.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5
programme.desc: Everyone's excited at the prospect of Leopard's Den's new arrival. Bash, Danny's old tutor and Rosie's Godfather, is coming from England to help Danny grow his veterinary practice.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 6
programme.desc: The Trevanions are delighted when Fatani asks Danny to take an aggressive hippo off his hands. As they prepare for its arrival Sarah gets a bit of a shock when her mother Caroline beats the hippo to the post.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 7
programme.desc: Business is looking up at Leopard's Den but Sarah is feeling agitated. Caroline thinks it because Simon, her ex husband and Evan and Olivia's Dad, is arriving from England to get married. But Sarah has other things on her mind.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 8
programme.desc: Danny is undertaking a drugs trial at Leopard's Den. But de-worming wildebeest isn't Caroline's idea of fun. She hates animals and finds the whole business mind-numbingly boring.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 9
programme.desc: Du Plessis is in a foul mood. It's his 60th birthday and he has no intentions of celebrating it. But the Trevanions have other ideas and Caroline is organising a surprise party.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 10
programme.desc: All is quiet at Leopard's Den as Sarah, Evan and Olivia gather at the hospital. Danny has been given the all clear to go home. But Du Plessis is still unconscious and seriously ill. Caroline keeps a tender vigil at his bedside.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 1
programme.desc: New lodges nearly break the family, but they learn that it's the animals which make Leopard's Den a success.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 2
programme.desc: Danny needs an assistant but fails to see that she's right under his nose; Sarah finds out that she needs her mum.

programme.title: Born Naughty?: Charlie and Billy
programme.desc: The doctors meet eight-year-old Charlie who can become so destructive and violent that his mum has had to call the police. After meeting him, Dr Ravi and the experts think that a controversial new diagnosis may be the reason for Charlie's behaviour.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: 65-year old Dave, a surf skier, is attacked and bitten by a Great White shark while training in the ocean. Dehydrated (after four days at sea), Margo needs urgent hospital care.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: A car crashes another car at a country intersection. It's situation critical with four people trapped. It turns out someone was running from the police and he was on drugs.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3
programme.desc: Tasmania Police is on high alert after a prisoner escapes from jail. The man is armed and dangerous. The Rescue Helicopter is called in to assist with the manhunt. Things turn deadly when they spot him.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: Hiker Robert had trained for over 6 months for the remote Cradle Mountain bush walk. With his young daughter in tow they set off on a 48 km walk. Three hours into the walk Roberts health takes a turn for the worse.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: A young man has flipped his quad bike and can't move his neck. Later that night, the crew is called to a suburban house because a DIY homebuilder has fallen through the roof in his house and there's a bone sticking out through his jeans.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: De Anna and her husband were celebrating their 50th wedding anniversary on board a luxury liner. The ship's doctor radios for help. But the liner is a long way out at sea. Can the rescue crew get to De Anna in time?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: 14 year-old motor-cross rider, Kacee gets the death wobbles and cartwheels over the top of his handle bars and hits the ground head first. He's now struggling to breath and is barely able to talk. Team Air Rescue needs to get Kacee to the hospital fast.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: Fishing buddies Scott, Wayne and Wayne's son Andrew head out to their favorite fishing spot, but when a freak wave hits their boat they have no choice but to SOS for help. Within minutes, the boat capsizes. Can the Air Rescue crew get to them in time?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3
programme.desc: 71 year-old retired nurse Sandra was exploring Tasmania's Cradle Mountain when she slipped and fractured her wrist. She's in excruciating pain and night is falling. Visibility is dangerously low. Can the rescue team get in close enough to get them out?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: Mountain bike fanatic, Blake was out riding when he clipped a tree and crashed into a rock. It's a time critical rescue mission. And what the rescue crew doesn't yet know is that Blake is about to take a turn for the worse.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: Motorbike rider, Lachlan was testing out his newly designed dirt-bike track when he lost control on a jump. His femur has been badly shattered. The Air Rescue crew is tasked with flying Lachlan to hospital but his medical dramas have only just begun.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: Retirees Diane and husband Gary were just a few hours into their Pacific Island cruise of a lifetime when disaster struck. Diane toppled down a set of stairs and now she's in need of urgent medical attention.

programme.title: The Boy Who Can't Forget
programme.desc: Twenty-year-old British student Aurelien is one of just a handful of people in the world who are baffling scientists with their ability to recall an incredible amount of their lives. He is the first Briton to go public with this extraordinary talent.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Blacktrail E-Bike
programme.desc: It is the new flagship from BMW. The K 1600 GT is tested. Much more expensive than the BMW, but with no emissions: The Blacktrail by PG.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Enduro Park Hechlingen
programme.desc: 26 hectares of off-road driving fun. Courses for total beginners and real pros. The BMW Enduropark in Hechlingen.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Triumph Thunderbird
programme.desc: A matte black chopper, the purist starter bike from Harley-Davidson. The Sportster 883 Iron is put to the test. Competition for the V2: a powerful 1.6 liter parallel twin, the Triumph Thunderbird.

programme.title: Motorcycles: BMW F 800 R
programme.desc: Today on motorcycles: We are testing the BMW F 800 R. A robust roadster with a lot of spirit, and even motorcycle world champions count on its agility.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Stereotypes on Two Wheels
programme.desc: It doesn't always have to be a Vespa. Three alternatives to the classic 125 scooter. City mobility in leaning angles without parking problems: with electro drive, with 500 cubic or with 3 wheels.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Triumph Speed Triple Carbon
programme.desc: Today on motorcycles: Carbon fiber on the Motorcycle - does that makes sense? We show what the formula 1-Carbon material is capable of.

programme.title: Motorcycles: KTM 990 Adventure
programme.desc: This time Motorcycles puts its eyes on Enduro bikes: the KTM 990 Adventure is Austrias answer to the bestselling BMW R 1200 GS. Can the Austrian all-rounder for streets, gravel roads and long distance beat the dominating Bavarian bike?

programme.title: Motorcycles: Custombike
programme.desc: Motorcycles presents the hottest bikes of Europe at the Custombike. The show in Bad Salzuflen is one of the leading fairs for exclusive motorcycles. This year more than 30.000 visitors from all over Europe have come to the event.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Harley Challenger
programme.desc: Motorcycles introduces you to the lightest power cruiser, the production bike with the biggest cubic capacity worldwide and a phenomenal all-rounder. Ralf Schtze reviews the Ducati Diavel with 162 hp and a weight of a bit more than 200 kg.

programme.title: Motorcycles: iMot Munich
programme.desc: At the IMOT in Munich, one of the major spring fairs, we look for the most important new developments from adventure travel with bikes, high-speed fun on super sports bikes.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Trikes
programme.desc: Anyone who thinks that you can put your feet up and relax, when you drive a trike, is quite mistaken. Motorcycles reviews various trikes for big boys including trikes with up to 200-hp car engines in the rear.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Triumph Tiger 800 XC
programme.desc: Motorcycles explores the British way to drive. Of course, that cant go without talking about the British cult brand Triumph. Our expert Ralf Schtze reviews their Tiger 800 and Tiger 1050.

programme.title: Motorheads: Ferruccio Lamborghini
programme.desc: Portrait of Ferruccio Lamborghini, who originally built tractors, but then moved on to found one of the most famous sports car factories in the world.

programme.title: Motorheads: Ferry Porsche
programme.desc: Portrait of Ferdinand Ferry Porsche, the father of the Porsche 911. He started his automobile legacy when he built the Porsche 935 after World War II.
